        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 6:03AM CDT by NWS Grand Forks ND</headline>
        <description>At 603 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Westwood Colony, or 11 miles northwest of Britton, moving northeast
at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gwinner, Forman, Cogswell, Stirum, Brampton, and Straubville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
